def: The quality or state of being sober.

Pertaining to, or discovered by, Regnier de Graaf, a Dutchphysician. Graafian follicles or vesicles, small cavities in whichthe ova are developed in the ovaries of mammals, and by the burstingof which they are discharged.
A kind of crystallite having a (slender) acicular form.
Ho; -- a word used in calling from a distant place; asportsman's halloo. Shak.
To appropriate wrongly; to use for a wrong purpose.
The quality or condition of being a duke; also, the personalityof a duke. Massinger.
A species of small opossum (Didelphus murina) ranging fromMexico to Brazil.
The hypothetical homogeneous cosmic material of the originaluniverse, supposed to have been differentiated into what arerecognized as distinct chemical elements.
Cinnamon stone, a variety of garnet. See Garnet.
To turn about a fixed point, usually the center or axis, as aspar or piece of timber; to turn; -- used also of any heavy body.
